<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer4613126793856900563">Andrew Seaward is the author of &quot;Some Are Sicker Than Others&quot;. Although he makes his living as a chemical engineer in the Oil &amp; Gas industry, his true passion is telling great stories through both acting and writing. He is a member and contributor of Benjy Dobrin Studios, the Cinematic Arts of Colorado, and the Denver Lighthouse Writers Workshop. He has written and acted in several short and featu</span>
  <span id="freeText4613126793856900563" style="display:none">Andrew Seaward is the author of "Some Are Sicker Than Others". Although he makes his living as a chemical engineer in the Oil &amp; Gas industry, his true passion is telling great stories through both acting and writing. He is a member and contributor of Benjy Dobrin Studios, the Cinematic Arts of Colorado, and the Denver Lighthouse Writers Workshop. He has written and acted in several short and feature length films, including "Drowning" which won an Award of Merit at the 2010 Indie Fest. </span>
